article.headline: Fordham 12, Yale 10
article.story: NEW YORK -- Adam Danko's 20-yard field goal with 14 seconds remaining gave Fordham a 12-10 victory over Yale on Saturday. Tom Mantee's 22-yard field goal in the first quarter gave the Bulldogs a 3-0 lead. The Rams (3-3) moved in front on John Skelton's 20-yard TD pass to Jason Caldwell in the first quarter. Yale (3-2) took a 10-7 lead when Bob Abare returned a fumble 86 yards for a touchdown in the third quarter. Fordham got within 10-9 on a safety in the third quarter. Skelton finished 31-for-45 for 291 yards. Running back Xavier Martin had 28 carries for 109 yards. Yale quarterback Ryan Fodor was 10-of-16 for 120 yards.
